A man was found fatally shot Sunday in an apartment Northeast Washington, D.C. police said. He was found about 11:15 a.m. on the floor of a unit in the 2300 block of 4th Street NE, according to an official in the Fifth Police District. He was suffering from a gunshot wound, and the death was being investigated as a homicide, the official said. A police spokeswoman said police had been sent there to check on his welfare. Police said he was dead when found. The apartment is in the Edgewood neighborhood, just north of Rhode Island Avenue NE, and a short distance from the Rhode Island Avenue Metrorail station.  This story has been updated. 